translated:
Cullberg, Carl Oscar Daniel, clergyman, pastor, Gothenburg, born August 5th, 1887 in Harestad, Goteborgs och Bohus Lan, firstborn of Archdeacon Johan Laurentius Cullberg and Harriet Sofia Rabe. Married Alma Floderus in 19xx. Children: Birgit (born 1913), nurse at Gothenburg Children's Hospital; Maj (born 1913), graduate in philosophy, married to music director Torsten Holmsten in Gothenburg; Stina (born 1914), gymnastics director, married to engineer Gösta Hildebrand in Forsbacka; Harriet (born 1916), map drawer in Gothenburg; Märta (born 1921), personnel consultant in Borås; Lars (born 1922), student. 

Education: Completed gymnasium studies in Latin in Gothenburg in 1906. Received a degree in theology and philosophy in 1907 and 1910 respectively. Ordained as a priest in 1911. Passed the doctoral exam in 1920. 

Career: Served as a church assistant in Fässberg in 1912, in Oscar Fredriks Parish in Gothenburg in 1918, as a pastor there in 1921, and as an archdeacon in 1945. Taught at the Women's Association Girls School from 1915-1936. Served as Superintendent of the Diocese from 1918-1930, Inspector of the Vasa Girls' School from 1930-1938, and teacher of the Kjellberg Girls' School since 1930. Became a member of the board in 1935 and chairman in 1943. Served as a member of the Gothenburg Public Elementary School Board from 1922-1935, a member of the church council since 1922, and chairman of the church council since 1935. Chairperson of the working committee for the Ah church youth home from 1937, member of the Deaconess Board of Sunday Schools since 1939, and chairman of the board for Gothenburg Home Economics School since 1943. 

Publications: The Importance of Baptism for the Christian Faith (1920). Received the Order of Vasa in 1932.
